And thus you see some few Branches, and rude Conclusion. Lineaments of that goodnesse and beneficialnesse of this diuine Ordinance, which the Spirit of God by the Pen of Salomon here pointeth vs vnto. A good Wife being, as you haue heard,
The best Companion in Wealth;
The fittest and readiest Assistant in Worke;
The greatest Comfort in Crosses and griefes;
The only warrantable and comfortable Meanes of Issue and posteritie;
A singular and soueraigne Remedie ordained by God against Incontinencie;
And the greatest Grace and Honour, that can be, to him that hath her.
In regard whereof euen
